The paper deals with the dictionary problem, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. It specifically focuses on solving this problem in external memory, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of hashing and buffer trees also suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), or cs.AL (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a lower bound in the cell-probe model suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
